#  == CHANGELOG ==
# - Version 0.9.8: (05 Jul 2022)
#   > Update Contact Details
# - Version 0.9.7: (15 Sep 2021)
#   > Fix division by 0 error
# - Version 0.9.6: (14 Sep 2021)
#   > Updated to Python 3 for latest Splunk Compatibility
# - Version 0.9.5: (24 Apr 2017)
#   > FIX: Changed TLS negotiation from TLSv1 to just TLS to support latest version using TLS 1.2
#   > Changed threading library to multiprocessing for performance improvements - 75% reduction load time
# - Version 0.9.4: (02 Apr 2017)
#   > Threaded version
#   > Output results immediately (no sorting of sessions or keys)
# - Version 0.9.3: (29 Mar 2017)
#   > Fix Python SSL wrapper to use TLSv1 instead of SSLv23 as it causes issues with NW SSL implementation
#   > Changed the loading of the JSON response to better handle enconding errors
#   > Use http://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/6.0/AdvancedDev/SetupExampleCredentials to avoid storing credentials in clear-text
#   > Two new configuration settings SLEEP & VERBOSE
#   > Changed read/write SID file functions to expand ENV vars (e.g. $SPLUNK_HOME)
#   > Changed main while True loop further so it recovers from every possible error
# - Version 0.9.2: (14 Dec 2014)
#   > Changed design to loop directly in script instead of being launched regularly via inputs.conf
#     - Currently sleeps 5 seconds between collections
#     - Should massively improve performance and reduce fall-behind situations
# - Version 0.9.1: (12 Dec 2012)
#   > FIX: Made the trailing "/" on the rest_host extraction optional
# - Version 0.9: (01 Dec 2012)
#   > Added code to populate event with host details based on the connection string (rest_host=<device_from_url>)
#     - Useful when pulling from multiple devices into the same Splunk infrastructure (muliple concentrator or brokers)
# - Version 0.8.9: (12 Nov 2012)
#   > Added "&expiry=0" to all queries to fix possible HTTP timeouts (Customer reported issue)
# - Version 0.8.7: (02 Nov 2012)
#   > Renamed SMTP saved searches to follow the same naming standard as the others
#   > Removed "| where cvp_reserved_count > 2" in OTHER traffic saved search
#     - Having all data can be handy for historic use cases
# - Version 0.8.6: (25 Oct 2012)
#   > Update to safe_str() to include UnicodeDecodeError exception and 'latin-1' encoding
# - Version 0.8.5: (15 Oct 2012)
#   > Added safe_str() code provided by Matt and updated where needed.
#   > Overall code is more resilient increased default MAX_META to 50000 (can possibly be higher)
# - Version 0.8.1: (02 Oct 2012)
#   > Fix NetWitness App dashboard to really count sourcetype=netwitness events only
# - Version 0.8: (25 Sep 2012)
#   > Changes in 9.8 break the script - Emergency Fix
#     - MAC Address values are no longer returned as integers
# - Version 0.7: (21 May 2012)
#   > Allow user to specify 'nwsdk' configuration file as an argument to allow for multiple instances of data collection
#     - If none is specified 'nwsdk.conf' will be used by default 
#   > Added "&flags=1" to summary query request to ignore cache.window.minutes as it impacts summary indexing results
#     - Should also improve performance as less data is returned with each query
# - Version 0.6.5: (19 Apr 2012 - Splunk IPO)
#   > Using summary indexing for APP, All, HTTP, Filetype, DNS, SMTP and OTHER Dashboards
#   > Created Saved Searches to Support summary index based dashboards
#   > Changed APP dashboard to show "Skipped" sessions instead of duplicates (mostly these are false-positives)
# - Version 0.6: (27 Feb 2012)
#   > Added error handling code on the get_sessions() function.
#     - Now, if a session contains data that can't be processed only that session is skipped
#     - Before the app would be stuck forever on those sessions, until they were manually skipped
# - Version 0.5.4: (15 Feb 2012)
#   > ISSUE: SSL not working out of the box - See README/App page
# - Version 0.5.3: (27 Jan 2012)
#   > FIX: Check last session id processed on each batch to make sure is as expected if not force correction (can cause some data loss)
#   > CHANGE: Changed duplicate sessionid search on App Dashboard to one day, otherwise it takes too long to run on larger environments
#   > FIX: Changed TRUNCATE to 0 in props.conf as some lines are greater than 10000 and were being broken incorrectly
# - Version 0.5.2: (18 Jan 2012)
#   > FIX: Converted all meta field names to lower case to avoid problems with timestamp parsing
#   > FIX: Processing stats were calculated wrong for the initial run (when LAST_SID_FILE is missing)
# - Version 0.5.1: (15 Nov 2011)
#   > Code added to map e-mail addresses to sender/recipient according to previous value of action meta
#     - For now the email address field is maintained for backwards compatibility
#   > Updated content of SMTP dashboard to use new fields too 
#   > CHANGE: Default for NO_SID_FILE_OPTION changed to -2 (read last <no_sid_seconds_back> seconds only)
#     - Previous default causing too much data import in some sites (not ideal as it pollutes Splunk buckets with old data)
#     - Added option to configure number of seconds to go back with no SID_FILE exists on first run
#   > Added processing stats message at execution end to help with performance metrics
#   > Updated App Dashboard to include some performance stats based on above generated data
#   > Updated App Dashboard to remove Splunk's LicenseUsage messages as they aren't app related
# - Version 0.5: (31 Oct 2011)
#   > Better error message on initial connection failures to help troubleshooting
#   > Map "."s to "_"s in meta names for better Splunk segmentation support
#     - Should be minimal impact as Splunk extraction already does this for the field extractions automatically
#   > Added code to read in custom/additional mappings from nwsdk.conf under [mappings] section (based on customer feedback)
#   > FIX: When reading "NO_SID_FILE_OPTION" from nwsdk.conf it wasn't being properly converted to an integer
# - Version 0.4.3: (18 Oct 2011)
#   > FIX: SMTP view wasn't parsing attachment names correctly when these contained spaces
# - Version 0.4.2: (14 Oct 2011)
#   > Added a View/Dashboard with OTHER traffic stats (shared globably)
#   > Added a View/Dashboard with File Type stats (shared globably)
# - Version 0.4.1: (05 Oct 2011)
#   > Added a View/Dashboard with DNS traffic stats (shared globably)
#   > Added a View/Dashboard with overall traffic stats (shared globably)
#   > Added a lookup for service number to name conversion (shared globably) Name: lookup_service
#     Usage: | lookup lookup_service service OUTPUT service_alias as service_alias
# - Version 0.4: (29 Sep 2011)
#   > FIX: Sort of session keys wasn't numeric (they are strings) which causes duplicate data at 100, 1000, 10000, 100000, etc...
#   > Added a View/Dashboard with some app and NW specific stats (shared globably)
#   > Added a View/Dashboard with HTTP traffic stats (shared globably)
#   > Added a View/Dashboard with SMTP traffic stats (shared globably)
# - Version 0.3: (21 Sep 2011)
#   > Implemented use of Splunk configuration files -> nwsdk.conf in ../default/ or ../local/ can now be used to configure NetWitness device
#     to allow the script to still run independent of Splunk the settings can still be configured below too
# - Version 0.2.2: (16 Sep 2011)
#   > FIX: On default settings if a LAST_SID_FILE didn't exist one would never be created causing the app never to read data
#   > Initial testing on Windows - Requires two entries in inputs.conf 
# - Version 0.2.1: (18 Aug 2011)
#   > Changed default LAST_SID_FILE path to /var/tmp to survive restarts (Doh!)
